<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>PoS fees get structure</strong></h2>



<p>The new guide also introduces a more structured fee regime for Point of Sale (PoS) withdrawals.</p>



<p>On-us withdrawals, using your bank or fintech’s own agent to get cash, will now cost ₦100 ($0.074) per ₦20,000 ($14.72).</p>



<p>For not-on-us withdrawals, using another bank or fintech’s own agent to get cash, customers will pay ₦100 ($0.074) per ₦20,000 ($14.72), in addition to a fee determined by the agent.</p>



<p>This represents a shift from the current informal pricing structure, where PoS withdrawals can cost as much as<a href="https://techcabal.com/2025/06/04/how-much-do-pos-agents-in-nigeria-make/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener"> ₦100 ($0.074) per ₦5,000 ($3.68)</a>.</p>



<p>PoS terminals are increasingly becoming the primary means of cash for many. In the first quarter of 2025, PoS terminals moved<a href="https://techcabal.com/2025/08/07/nigerians-use-pos-more-than-atms-2025/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener"> ₦116.79 billion ($85.97 million) per day</a>.</p>



